#Question b: If you have never worked for a software development company, 
which of the four test activities do you think you are best qualified for? (test design, automation, execution, evaluation)

I think  I would be qualified for testing design because I think it is a really important part, help so much about knowing the test
make it easier to test.

Test design is a process that describes “how” testing should be done. It includes processes for the identifying test cases by enumerating steps of the defined test conditions. 
The testing techniques defined in test strategy or plan is used for enumerating the steps.
